## Summary of the Full Flow

```
DB tables (role grants)
        ↓
auth_controller builds collection_agents dict
        ↓
JWT contains {"RMS_ANALYTICS": ["reviewer"], ...}
        ↓
User sends chat message with collection_name="RMS_ANALYTICS"
        ↓
permission_check_node reads JWT → finds "reviewer" for "RMS_ANALYTICS" → grants access
        ↓
sql_generator_node calls build_schema_description("RMS_ANALYTICS", "reviewer", "2633", "EAG")
        ↓
schema description includes "WHERE Resource = 2633" for all tables
        ↓
LLM writes SQL with that filter naturally
        ↓
sql_validator_node confirms it
        ↓
sql_executor_node runs it → returns only emp 2633's rows
        ↓
output_formatter sends chart/table/text to frontend
```

Run the verification query at the end of Step 6 first. If it returns correct rows, proceed to Postman Test 1. Each test tells you exactly which layer to debug if something is wrong.